title: Judas Priest - Painkiller
description: Released in 1990, Painkiller is a thunderous declaration of Judas Priest’s place at the pinnacle of heavy metal. Opening with Scott Travis's iconic double-kick drum assault, the track explodes into blistering guitars, Halford’s piercing vocals, and apocalyptic lyricism. A relentless speed metal anthem, it marked a reinvention of the band’s sound and remains one of their most celebrated tracks. Painkiller isn’t just a song — it’s a war cry for metal fans.
